<span id="freeTextContainer14228599159444293605">Not a textbook! Thank heavens for that!! <br/><br/>A plain and simple story of a boy raised in Bangladesh and his struggle to uplift the people in the streets. To bring about an economic revolution that benefits not just a handful in the country, but uplifts each and every citizen, for true progress of the nation. <br/><br/>And through this story, he then explains the concept of micro-finance, the underlying premise of the book, and Yunus&apos; brain child. If you are into Economics and Finance and want to learn the con</span>
  <span id="freeText14228599159444293605" style="display:none">Not a textbook! Thank heavens for that!! <br /><br />A plain and simple story of a boy raised in Bangladesh and his struggle to uplift the people in the streets. To bring about an economic revolution that benefits not just a handful in the country, but uplifts each and every citizen, for true progress of the nation. <br /><br />And through this story, he then explains the concept of micro-finance, the underlying premise of the book, and Yunus' brain child. If you are into Economics and Finance and want to learn the concept of Micro-finance, this is your book. The background story (his autobiography) is actually just narrated to help readers grasp the importance and the full-length of the concept of his idea, his banking technique, and micro-finance. He aims to deliver the lesson across and succeeds in doing so quite marvellously. So, you basically grasp concepts of finance without the humdrum of going through textbooks!! Quite a feat.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14228599159444293605" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

