<div id="review_548092627" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/548092627" />
    <a title="Jr Bacdayan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16587936-jr-bacdayan"><img alt="Jr Bacdayan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552066595p2/16587936.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/548092627?book_show_action=true">Feb 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jr Bacdayan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jr Bacdayan" href="/user/show/16587936-jr-bacdayan">Jr Bacdayan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer548092627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6634016973810317017">Banker to the Poor is the autobiography of 2006 Nobel Peace Prize Winner Muhammad Yunus. He&apos;s a Bangladeshi banker, economist, visionary, philanthropist, a great man. It&apos;s basically about his experiences and the challenges that he faced when he founded the Grameen Bank, a bank focusing on Micro Finance or banking focusing on the development and helping people below the poverty line. Yunus also details his development of the idea of Micro Credit, or loans for the poorest of the poor. It&apos;s one man</span>
  <span id="freeText6634016973810317017" style="display:none">Banker to the Poor is the autobiography of 2006 Nobel Peace Prize Winner Muhammad Yunus. He's a Bangladeshi banker, economist, visionary, philanthropist, a great man. It's basically about his experiences and the challenges that he faced when he founded the Grameen Bank, a bank focusing on Micro Finance or banking focusing on the development and helping people below the poverty line. Yunus also details his development of the idea of Micro Credit, or loans for the poorest of the poor. It's one man's journey towards the change he envisions. Truly, inspirational. A great read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6634016973810317017" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


